                <h3 id="planning">Planning</h3>
                <h4>Design Exploration</h4>
                <div class="row paragraph-spacing">
                    <div class="col-12">
                        <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                            The purpose of the design exploration was to find new and creative ways of utilising one or more of
                            the API's listed on the State Library of Queensland's website. The API I went with was the Quuensland
                            Mining Accidents 1882-1945 as this was one of the more complete and consistent API's.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row paragraph-spacing">
                    <div class="col-6 process-list-div">
                        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
                            <strong>Process</strong><br>
                            <hr class="my-4">
                            <span class="process-list" style="padding-top: 1.5rem;">
                                <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i>
                                Ideation
                            </span><br>
                            <span class="process-list">
                                <i class="fas fa-paint-brush"></i>
                                Design
                            </span><br>
                            <span class="process-list">
                                <i class="fas fa-theater-masks"></i>
                                Presentation & Pitch
                            </span>
                            <hr class="my-4">
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-6">
                        <img src="/img/posterFilePNG.png" alt="Picture of a poster" style="width: 100%; border: 1px solid grey;">
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row paragraph-spacing">
                    <div class="col-12">
                        <p>
                            <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i>
                            <strong>Ideation.</strong>
                            It took quite some time coming up with an idea that felt both unique and engaging.
                            Going through the ideation process I worked through several iterations on the original ideas
                            trying to find an unique angle, but due to limitations in the API's I scrapped most of them.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            As a tool for coming up with an idea I started to reverse engineer the API's looking for
                            coherent data and consistency in data entry, which resulted in only a few API's standing out.
                            One of the stronger API's was the Quuensland Mining Accidents 1882-1945, which after bouncing
                            some ideas off a classmate led to the concept of teaching kids about workplace health and
                            safety (WHS) and geology.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Knowing that in order to create an engaging teaching platform for kids I should
                            consider including a gamification aspect to the platform. The first idea was to have the
                            users control the miners, but to avoid creating to much game art I quickly scoped down
                            to instead have the users control the foreman of a 19th century coal mine.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row paragraph-spacing">
                    <div class="col-12">
                        <p>
                            <i class="fas fa-paint-brush"></i>
                            <strong>Design.</strong>
                            Because the assignment was to produce a digital poster to present the idea, and a lack of
                            digital drawing skills on my part, I chose to go for a forgiving comic art style.
                            To avoid creating to many assets, I came to the conclusion of using the foreman's office
                            as the landing screen of the platform. The initial idea was to implement three elements,
                            1. A book for researching establishing a timeline, 2. a computer for research, 3. a notepad
                            for putting together the pieces. At this point in time the platform was going to be a game
                            that let you research and figure out what happened to people during a mining accident. Given
                            that the game were to take place in the 19th century, the computer would at a later stage
                            have to be swapped out with something else.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            I quickly did some research into old mining offices, and found some inspirational pictures.
                            Based on these I put together a wireframe and was happy enough with the first draft to
                            start designing the final poster in Photoshop.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
