            <p>
                As for the outcome of the project, we managed to put together a decent demo with scalable in-game cycles
                that is only dependent on the number of Workplace Health and Safety policies added to the files.
                The game is somewhat bare-bones in terms of functionality, but it deliverers on the core mechanics
                and conveys the message as wanted. All in all, I feel the amount of work we were able to do in the given
                time period and only a small amount of knowledge to Node.js up front did result in a decent project.
                Due to the project being a game there are so many minor details that need to work properly in order to
                achieve a 'game feel'. I feel like we came close to implementing this game feel but ideally, given some
                more time, we could have really made the game impactful.
            </p>
